<HEADLINE> Chinese Takes First Two Golds at Asian Women Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, October 27 (Xinhua/OANA) -- Chinese fencers dominated
the first day's competition of the Fifth Asian Women's Fencing
Championships on Monday, by clinching both 1-2 finishes in the
foil and epee events.
</P>
<P>
Favorite Xiao Yanhua took the individual foil title after she
beat her teammate Wang Huifeng 15-8 in the final.
</P>
<P>
Ye Lin of China and Shin Gwi-Ryeon of South Korea shared third
in the foil.
</P>
<P>
In the epee competition, Liang Shuxian played more offensive
and made a 15-4 easy victory over He Jiali from Hong Kong, China,
for the champion. China's Zhu Meifang and South Korea's Lee
Myung-Hee placed third.
</P>
<P>
A total of 43 fencers from six countries and regions, also
including Kazakhstan, the Philippines and Chinese Taipei, are
competing the two-day four-event championships.
</P>
<P>
The foil and epee team finals will be held on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
