<HEADLINE> Asprilla Hopes to Join Match Against Barcelona </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Faustino Asprilla of Columbia is
looking forward to a return match against Barcelona on November
26, inspired by a fast recoverence from a groin muscle tear.
</P>
<P>
The Newcastle playmaker injuried his groin muscle when he was
converting a free-kick in a Champions-Cup match against Dynamo
Kiev when the Magpies tied 2-2. He had not been expected to come
back until December.
</P>
<P>
The genius Columbian played a hat-trick in the first-leg clash
on September 17 when the English Premier club beat Barcelona 3-2.
</P>
<P>
Newcastle lost 1-0 at PSV Eindhoven last Wednesday after
Asprilla's absence.
</P>
<P>
To gain top place in the group, Newcastle needs a maximus
points from meetings with Eindhoven and Kiev before it faces
Barcelona. 
</P>
</TEXT>
