<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Calls on Algeria to Implement Reform Promise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 27 (Xinhua) -- France today called on Algerian
government to implement its plan on political, economic and social
reforms, and took note of the criticism by Algerian parties about
the situation of the local elections held last week in the
country.
</P>
<P>
The French Minister of European Affairs Pierre Moscovici
strongly criticized on Sunday the situation of the local elections
held last Thursday, in which the Algerian opposition denounced
"flagrant and massive fraud."
</P>
<P>
"While the 15 European Union countries can approve an
institutional process which begins to improve (in Algeria), one
can also be sometimes unsatisfied with the way in which democracy
moves ahead (in the country), notably in case of the latest local
elections which showed a certain step backward in comparison with
previous votings, " said French Foreign Ministry spokesman
Jacques Rummelhardt.
</P>
<P>
He said that France had taken note of the criticism by Algerian
parties about the lack of transparency in the local elections last
week.
</P>
<P>
"What is essential is that these local elections should have
let Algerians mark their rejection of violence as well as their
hope to overcome by peace and voting the crisis which their
country knows," said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
France hopes that elected institutions could allow Algerians to
reconcile among themselves and "concretize the objectives of
economic, social and political reform and opening which the
Algerian authorities have announced." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
