<HEADLINE> Siemerink Beats Martin in First Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Dutch Jan Siemerink Monday came
back to upset American Todd Martin 4-6, 7-6 (8-6), 6-2 and moved
into the second round at the Paris Indoor Open.
</P>
<P>
Siemerink meets Britain's fourth-seeded Greg Rusedski in the
second round.
</P>
<P>
The 1.98m Martin, ranked 52th in the world, lost his way after
squandering the match points and dropping his opening service game
in the third set.
</P>
<P>
The 108th-ranked Siemerink had arrived in Paris having won just
one match in his previous four tournaments, but put Martin under
pressure from the start.
</P>
<P>
In another of the first day matches, Sweden's Thomas Johansson
defeated fellow qualifier Sjeng Schalken of the Netherlands 6-4,
6-7 (2-7), 6-3. He will face his compatriot Jonas Bjorkman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
