<HEADLINE> DPRK Condemns U.S.-S. Korea Military Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, October 27 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK) today condemned a joint U.S.-South Korean
military exercise as an aggressive maneuver for a possible
surprise attack.
</P>
<P>
"Facts prove that the exercise is not an 'annual exercise
to 'test the command, control and communications systems,' but an
aggressive maneuver for launching a surprise attack on the DPRK,"
a spokesman for the DPRK Foreign Ministry said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
"No one can predict when the current military drill will
develop into real war against the DPRK," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The military drill, code-named "Foal Eagle," began on Monday
and is scheduled to end on November 6.
</P>
<P>
"In order to defend the security of the country and the people,
we will not rule out sacred war against the aggressors, " the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
He warned that the United States and South Korea "had better
act with discretion, mindful that today's one wrong step may
result in an irrevocable repentance." 
</P>
</TEXT>
