<DOCNO> XIE19971028.0025 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> WTO: No Truly "Global" Trading System Without Full </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Director-General of the World
Trade Organization (WTO) Renato Ruggiero said here today that the
world can never have a truly "global" trading system without the
full integration of the least-developed countries.
</P>
<P>
Ruggiero was speaking at the opening session of an inter-agency
meeting on Integrated Initiatives for Least Developed Countries'
(LDCs) Trade development jointly sponsored by six
inter-governmental agencies, which are WTO, UNCTAD, the
International Trade Center (ITC, a joint subsidiary of UNCTAD and
WTO), the United Nations Development Program (UNDP), the
International Monetary Fund (IMF) and the World Bank.
</P>
<P>
"It is an enormously important meeting," Ruggiero told
participants from WTO members and representatives and ministers
from 39 LDCs, present at the meeting to be held on October 27-28.
"It is important because for the first time we are bringing all
the energy of the multilateral system to bear on the problem of
economic marginalization."
</P>
<P>
"It is important because without the full integration of the
LDCs we can never have a truly "global" trading system," Ruggiero
went on. "And it is important because it represents a tangible
sign of the extent to which your countries have embraced openness,
integration and trade as the keys to economic development."
</P>
<P>
Ruggiero called on the participants to produce meaningful
results, results that will be of real and practical significance
to the LDCs.
</P>
<P>
He gave three reasons why the meeting should produce concrete
and practical results: first, by opening up new market access
opportunities for LDCs exports; second, by designing an integrated
approach to building trade capacity which reflects the real needs
of the LDCs themselves; and third, by using new technology to open
a window of new opportunity between North and South, a window
through which information, knowledge and ideas can flow freely and
productively.
</P>
<P>
Participants will have a series of roundtable sessions during
the two-day meeting. The secretariats of the six agencies taking
part in the meeting will offer assistance in their respective
areas of expertise to the 12 LDCs for which roundtable sessions
have been organized.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, WTO members will have a chance to announce
steps they are taking, on an autonomous basis, to enhance their
market access for imports for LDCs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
