<HEADLINE> Two More Sugar Acquisitions for AFB </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 27 (Xinhua) - Associated British Foods today
announced two further acquisitions in the drive to build its
presence in the growing markets of China and Poland.
</P>
<P>
Through its British Sugar Overseas (BSO) subsidiary, the
company is acquiring a 70 percent holding in the former Xianghou
Country Luoxio Sugar Factory in Guangxi province, south western
China.
</P>
<P>
Under the terms of the joint venture, British Sugar's 13
million pounds (20.8 million US dollars) will be used to develop
the factory's capacity up to 80,000 tons of sugar per year from
its current capacity of 20,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The Glinojeck Sugar Factory, one of Poland's largest and most
modern units, will invest 10 million pounds (16 million US
dollars) in a 41 percent stake with the intention of taking a
majority holding within six months.
</P>
<P>
Together with its partners, the North East Handling Company and
the UK's Treasury Ministry, it will develop the factory from its
current 750 tons per day of sugar, to over 1000 tons per day.
</P>
</TEXT>
