<HEADLINE> China Calls for Action-Oriented International </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 27 (Xinhua) -- In strengthening
inter-state cooperation in drug control as well as in adopting a
balanced drug control strategy against the illicit supply of and
demand for narcotics, the international community needed to be
more action-oriented and enhance international and interregional
Multi-level cooperation, Chinese delegate Diao Mingsheng stressed
here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the Third Committee (Social, Humanitarian and
Cultural) of the fifty-second session of the General Assembly,
Diao Mingsheng said the international community had achieved new
progress in implementing the Global Program of Action and relevant
international conventions and in strengthening the cooperation in
the control and interdiction of narcotics drugs and psychotropic
substances.
</P>
<P>
Diao said on the occasion of the tenth anniversary of the 1988
Convention against Illicit Traffic in Narcotic Drugs and
Psychotropic Substances before the advent of the 21st century, it
would be necessary for the international community to deliberate
on the global drug situation over the last decade and express to
mankind its strong political will to improve and enhance
international cooperation in drug control.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese delegate said the political will of the
international community to strengthen cooperation had been well
reflected in the preparatory work for the Special Session of the
General Assembly on drug control and the discussions and
consultations were now well under way on documents for the
Session.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the Special session of the General
Assembly on drug control to be held next year would be more
result-oriented and produce documents that would, in a positive,
practical and effective way, constitute the basis for guiding the
international drug-control cooperation in the next century.
</P>
</TEXT>
