<HEADLINE> Qatari Foreign Minister Visits UAE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Qatar Foreign Minister Hamad
Ibin Jassim Jaber al Thani arrived here this afternoon for a brief
visit, the United Arab Emirates' (UAE) Wam news agency said.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that the minister's visit was part of Qatar's
efforts to expound to its Arab neighbors its insistence in hosting
the controversial Fourth Middle East and North Africa economic
conference in its capital Doha next month.
</P>
<P>
The conference, traditionally attended by Arab states, Israel
and their major partners in the world, was strongly opposed by
Syria, Lebanon, the Palestinian Authority, the UAE and Saudi
Arabia for lack of progress in the Mideast peace process.
</P>
<P>
Those Arab countries held Israel's Netanyahu government
responsible for the expansion of Jewish settlements, confiscation
of Arab lands, demolition of Palestinian houses and worsening of
the situation in the region.
</P>
<P>
The Qatari minister is expected to explain to UAE officials the
reasons for Doha's determination to convene the gathering despite
opposition from most Arab states.
</P>
<P>
Qatar has argued that such a meeting is aimed at boosting trade
cooperation among world countries and it is "purely an economic
one" and should not be connected with political issues. 
</P>
