<HEADLINE> Canada's Sable Gas Project Gets Go-ahead From Panel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, October 27 (Xinhua) -- A multi-billion-dollar gas
project off Canada's east coast got a go-ahead today from a panel
of energy and environmental regulators.
</P>
<P>
The panel, led by Canada's National Energy Board, recommended
that the 2-billion-dollar (1.4 billion USD) Sable gas project be
allowed to proceed.
</P>
<P>
After months of hearings, the panel also approved the
one-billion-dollar Maritimes and Northeast Pipeline, which will
carry gas through Nova Scotia and New Brunswick provinces to the
United States.
</P>
<P>
Gas pools around Canada's Sable Island are estimated to contain
142 billion cubic meters of gas, more than twice Canada's
consumption in 1993.
</P>
<P>
The total potential of Scotian Shelf off Nova Scotia is thought
to be at more than three times of that. 
</P>
</TEXT>
