<HEADLINE> Heads of Angola's Warring Sides to Meet in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Angolan President Eduardo Dos
Santos is scheduled to meet Jonas Savimbi, chairman of the former
rebel movement the National Union for the Total Independence of
Angola (UNITA) here in November.
</P>
<P>
Dos Santos made the announcement today at a press conference
after a meeting with his counterparts from Gabon, Democratic
Congo, Congo Brazzaville here in the capital.
</P>
<P>
According to him, the two sides have been making preparations
for the meeting, which he said, was not under the pressure of the
United States, nor the peace process observers or international
community.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will meet so long as it is conducive to solving
issues of the country, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Angolan government was not opposed to holding meetings
with Savimbi, the president said, adding that a government
delegation has gone to central Angola where the UNITA
headquarters are located, to make arrangements for the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The forthcoming meeting will be the fifth between Dos Santos
and Savimbi since the Lusaka Peace Accord was signed in November
1994 to end the civil war. It will be their first meeting held
in Angola. 
