<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Woman Injured by Crocodile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 27 (Xinhua) -- A Tanzanian elderly
woman has been seriously wounded after being attacked by a
man-eater crocodile at her home village.
</P>
<P>
The woman, whose right hand was fractured with multiple
injuries, is under medical treatment in the Tanzanian capital of
Dar es Salaam.
</P>
<P>
The 52-year-old woman named Zena Selemani Kondo said she was
attacked last weekend by the crocodile as she was drawing water
from the Ruvu River in the eastern region of Morogoro.
</P>
<P>
"The huge reptile caught my arm as I lowered to collect
water," she said, adding that the crocodile then tried to pull
her into the river.
</P>
<P>
Alarmed by the scene, two men on each side of the river
immediately came to pounce on the crocodile and pull the victim
out.
</P>
<P>
The crocodile was later confused and started searching its
prey wildly but to no avail, the women added.
</P>
<P>
The river is notorious for similar incidents in which several
people have lost their lives.
</P>
<P>
The woman from Kipera Village was attended by doctors from a
military hospital nearby and then transferred to the Muhimbili
Orthopaedic Institute in Dar es Salaam. 
</P>
</TEXT>
