<HEADLINE> Hezbollah to Announce New Recruiting Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Lebanese Hezbollah secretary-
general Sheikh Nasrallah has said that he would announce soon a
new recruiting policy for the resistance, local newspaper the
Daily Star reported today.
</P>
<P>
In a speech last week commemorating the 40th day of his son's
death during a battle against Israeli troops, Nasrallah said that
he would announce the details of the new policy this week, the
paper quoted an unidentified source as saying.
</P>
<P>
Nasrallah said that Hezbollah, or Party of God, had studied
carefully and taken into consideration all factors relating to the
more lenient new policy, according to the paper.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah would be more open for any "honest Lebanese" to join
in a comfortable way, regardless of their religion or political
affiliation, Nasrallah said.
</P>
<P>
"This announcement concerns all those wishing to participate
in military operations," he said.
</P>
<P>
However, he stressed that the war against Israel was not only
dependent on weapons, but on reviving the unity of the Arabs as
well in facing the Israeli menace.
</P>
<P>
"This is the responsibility of all Islamic movements and
political parties in the Arab world, regardless of their ideology
or background," he said.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah, backed by Iran, is fighting to drive the
2,500-strong Israeli occupation army out of south Lebanon.
</P>
</TEXT>
