<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Grain Harvest Nearly Conclude </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Russian state grain production
totaled 84.7 million tons, 16.3 million tons more than 1996,
and the yield had risen 0.3 tons to 1.94 tons per hectare, the
Interfax quoted Ministry of Agriculture and Food's crop chief Ivan
Gridasov as reporting today.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, only 9 percent of the crop area,
600,000 hectares of grain, left to harvest as of October 25.
</P>
<P>
Gridasov said that 294,000 hectares of maize had been cleared,
44 percent of the crop area and 104,000 hectares more than a year
ago.
</P>
<P>
Russia is expected to produce about 85 million tons of grain
in all this year, the report said.
</P>
<P>
However, Gridasov said, the sugarbeet harvest was causing
serious concern. Machinery could not be used properly due to heavy
rains in some areas, and just 480,000 hectares of crop had been
harvested, 53 percent of the target and 282,000 hectares less than
a year ago.
</P>
<P>
He noted that farmers had harvested 1.86 million hectares of
sunflower, 681,000 hectares less than last year, 94,000 hectares
of flax-fiber, 39,000 hectares less, and 251,000 hectares of
potatoes, 49,000 hectares less.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, seed reserves in Russia as a whole contained 9.243
million tons of grain and grain legume seeds, 96 percent of the
requirement.
</P>
<P>
Gridasov said there would be a shortage of some 300,000 tons
of grain seed, 20,000 tons of which maize seed, for next year's
crop. 
</P>
</TEXT>
