<HEADLINE> China Sees Dialogue on Economic Cooperation Important </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 27 (Xinhua) -- It is all the more
necessary to strengthen dialogue for international economic
cooperation in the lack of dynamism for the cooperation, a Chinese
delegate told the United Nations today.
</P>
<P>
China's Deputy Representative to the U. N. Wang Qun said at a
time globalization is advancing and interdependence between
nations is deepening, the dialogue is becoming more important.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks at a meeting of the Economic and Financial
Committee which was working on the agenda "Renew the Dialogue on
Strengthening International Economic Cooperation through
Partnership".
</P>
<P>
Wang said U.N. member states should reach a new understanding
of international cooperation in a new situation, with a genuine
global partnership functioning on the basis of mutual benefits.
</P>
<P>
He said it is imperative to respect the right of the developing
countries to choose their mode of development and that the
dialogue should be action-oriented and productive.
</P>
<P>
"The adoption of the Agenda for Development and the review of
the follow-up to major international conferences should give much
impetus to our efforts to explore ways and means to transform
consensuses and commitments into actions," Wang added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
