<HEADLINE> Cambodian Parliament Approves Party Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The Cambodian National
Assembly approved a political party law today that is vital for
the general elections scheduled for May next year.
</P>
<P>
Under the law, a minimum of 80 Cambodian citizens above the age
of 18, who have a permanent address in Cambodia, can form a
political party; and a party with a minimum of 4,000 members from
10 provinces and municipalities of Cambodia can register for the
elections.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia currently has about 20 parties, with the Cambodian
People's Party and the FUNCINPEC, which respectively have 3 and 2
million members, are considered to be the biggest parties.
</P>
<P>
Another crucial electoral law for the elections is subject to
the approval of the parliament in November. The law, which will
decide if the ousted prime minister Prince Norodom Ranariddh can
take part in the polls, is bound to arouse wide attention. 
</P>
