<HEADLINE> Damming in Three Gorges Well on Schedule </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The damming of the Yangtze
River has passed the toughest stage, and the final damming before
4 p.m. on November 8 is sure to succeed, a senior engineer said
today.
</P>
<P>
Between 8 a.m. and 4 p.m. on November 8, the remaining 40
meters of the dam opening will be sealed, said He Gong, deputy
general manager of the Yangtze River Three Gorges Development
Corporation.
</P>
<P>
By October 23, the river flow had been reduced to a width of
130 meters, and by the early morning hours of October 27, the
space was down to only 40 meters.
</P>
<P>
According to specialists, the most difficult work was to reduce
the opening from 100 meters to 50 meters because of the water
depth and fierce current.
</P>
<P>
It is predicted that from October 26 to 31, river flow through
the Three Gorges area will be about 10,000 cubic meters per
second, and the flow will eventually slow down, a good omen for
the damming operation, He Gong said.
</P>
<P>
With the 40-m opening forming, 85 percent of the river now
flows through the diversion channel on the southern bank of the
river. 
</P>
</TEXT>
