<HEADLINE> Russia Endorses Japanese Policy on Bilateral Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Russia voiced full support for
Japan's "trustful, mutually beneficial and toward the future"
diplomatic policy with Russia, Federation Council Chairman Yegor
Semeonovich Stroyev told Itar-Tass news agency today.
</P>
<P>
Japan's stand is constructive and encourages the development of
Russian-Japanese cooperative relations, the chairman said.
</P>
<P>
Leaders from the two countries met at the Denver Summit of
Eight in June this year. The meeting made it possible for both
sides to prevent the closing of the "iron curtain" and provided a
way to approach and resolve differences.
</P>
<P>
The upcoming informal talks between the two leaders will be the
basis for setting a new stage for bilateral relations and should
provide specific plans to embody the relations, Stroyev said.
</P>
<P>
He called for strengthening bilateral economic cooperation and
a peaceful settlement for all differences.
</P>
<P>
Stroyev made the remarks on the eve of his first visit to
Japan. He is to lead a delegation from the Federation Council to
Japan on October 29 for a formal visit. 
</P>
