<HEADLINE> Harbors in Fujian Province Fulfill Production Tasks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Harbors in southeast China's
Fujian Province have transported a total volume of 15.1 million
tons of goods by the end of September, fulfilling the yearly
target three months earlier than planned.
</P>
<P>
Among the total volume of cargo transported, imported goods
accounted for 9.58 million tons and exported goods, 5,53 million
tons, up 58.1 percent and 38.2 percent, respectively, compared
with the same period of last year, according to the statistics of
the Port Office of the Fujian provincial government.
</P>
<P>
In terms of international ocean shipping containers, the
harbors handled a total of 576,000 TEUs, up 34.5 percent from the
same period in 1996. 
</P>
