<DOCNO> XIE19971028.0085 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Able to Pay off WB Loans for Xiaolangdi Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAOLANGDI, October 28 (Xinhua) -- China has the ability to pay
back the one billion US dollars in loans from the World Bank
granted for the Xiaolangdi water control project, Vice-minister of
Water Resources Zhang Jiyao told reporters today.
</P>
<P>
The Yellow River, the second longest in China, was successfully
dammed this morning at Xiaolangdi in central China's Henan
Province.
</P>
<P>
All the loans will be paid off 17 years after the Xiaolangdi
reservoir is put into use, Zhang said. World Bank loans account
for only a third of the project's total investment, he said.
</P>
<P>
An assessment of the value of electric power and water in the
future indicates that China will have the financial strength to
repay the WB loans, he said.
</P>
<P>
Despite the fact the river flow has decreased over the past
years due to less precipitation and an increasing number of water
projects at the upper reaches, the Chinese government will ensure
electricity generation by adopting new water-allocation plans,
promoting water-saving industries and diverting more water into
the Yellow River, according to the vice-minister. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
