<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 15:30 GMT, October 28 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Foreign Minister David Levy said today he
is still not sure if he will travel to the United States for talks
with Palestinian deputy leader Mahmoud Abbas (Abu Mazen).
</P>
<P>
Speaking after meeting with a delegation of the European
Parliament, Levy said he is still waiting for a meeting of the
inner cabinet, to be convened tomorrow, to formulate guidelines
for future negotiations with the Palestinian side.
</P>
<P>
If the parameters for concessions that Israel is expected to
make and the commitments to be undertaken by the Palestinian
National Authority (PNA) are defined, Levy will be able to leave
for Washington in time for talks to begin early next
week. (Israel-Levy-PNA)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- A Tajik military outpost on the border with
Uzbekistan was attacked today and four Tajik border guards were
wounded, the Itar-Tass news agency reported from Dushanbe, capital
of Tajikistan.
</P>
<P>
The Tajik border troops fired back following the attack from
Uzbek territory.
</P>
<P>
There have been reports recently claiming that the Tajik
anti-government troops have made Uzbekistan their base. A former
anti-government troop leader admitted that they have been assisted
by some Uzbek military officers. (Tajikistan-Uzbekistan-Conflict)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LUSAKA -- Zambian President Frederick Chiluba declared here
today that a coup has been aborted and the situation in the
capital is "firmly under control".
</P>
<P>
A defense official told Xinhua on condition of anonymity that
the coup has been aborted and all the soldiers involved in the
coup have been arrested.
</P>
<P>
Soldiers led by Captain Solo (only name) who announced the
coup at seven o'clock local time through Zambia News Broadcasting
Corporation surrounded the State House, where President Frederick
Chiluba lives, and the buildings of Zambia News Agency have been
captured by anti-government soldiers. (Zambia-Coup)
</P>
