<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Problems Require Serious Work in Xiaolangdi Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAOLANGDI, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Now that the Xiaolangdi
damming project has been successfully completed, three pressing
problems that remain will have to be tackled with the concerted
efforts of both Chinese and foreign parties involved,
Vice-minister of Water Resources Zhang Jiyao told reporters today.
</P>
<P>
In preparation for the flood season of 1998, cofferdams along
the upper reaches of the Yangtze River must be constructed to a
height of 185 meters before the floodwaters come.
</P>
<P>
Second, the resettlement of local residents will become more
urgent as a result of the rising water levels after the damming. A
total of one billion yuan (120 million US dollars) has been put
into the resettlement program.
</P>
<P>
Finally, machinery and electric equipment to be installed at
the dam must arrive according to schedule and in good condition.
</P>
<P>
Zhang expressed his belief that all the problems can be solved
with the full cooperation of both Chinese and foreign entities.
</P>
</TEXT>
