<HEADLINE> Int'l Conference on Crime Prevention Opens in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, October 28 (Xinhua) -- A four-day international
conference on the promotion of multi-lateral cooperation on crime
prevention opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Some 500 anti-crime experts from 24 countries, mainly
Asian countries, attended the annual conference sponsored by the
Tokyo-based Asian Crime Prevention Foundation (ACPF).
</P>
<P>
Symposiums will discuss a five-point agenda including the
improvement of cross-border cooperation in investigation and
prosecution, the extradition of fugitives and the suppression of
drug-related crimes in Asia.
</P>
<P>
The ACPF, a non-governmental organization authorized by the
United Nations, was founded in 1982 with the aim of deterring
crime and contributing to peace and stability in Asia. 
</P>
