<HEADLINE> Top Spanish Swimmer Lopez Zubero Retires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Spanish swimming star Martin
Lopez Zubero has retired, it was reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The sports daily Marca said Lopez Zubero relayed his decision
to leave the sport by mailing his Spanish club via the Internet
from his American home.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old won the world championships 200 meters
backstroke in 1991 and the same distance a year later at the
Barcelona Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Lopez Zubero, who has been the Florida-based swimmer, also won
the 1994 world 100 backstroke title.
</P>
<P>
Lopez Zubero ended his major championship career in August at
the European swimming championships in Seville, Spain, by winning
his fourth European 100 meters backstroke gold medal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
