<DOCNO> XIE19971028.0094 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Benefits of Xiaolangdi Dam Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAOLANGDI, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Experts say that the
completion of the Xiaolangdi Multi-purpose Dam Project will
effectively control floods and protect people's lives and property.
</P>
<P>
The Xiaolangdi Dam Project, the largest of its kind ever built
on the Yellow River, China's second longest river, is meant to
control the river at the place where the riverbed of the lower
reaches has been rising at a rate of ten centimeters a year.
</P>
<P>
Due to the large amount of sediment deposited from the upper
reaches that pass through the eroded Loess Plateau, many cities
along the river are several meters, often as many as ten, below
water level of the river.
</P>
<P>
Xiaolangdi is situated in a prime position for flood and
sediment control of the Yellow River. Upon completion, the
Xiaolangdi Dam and Reservoir Project will effectively mitigate
catastrophic floods, as well as control silting, ice jams,
irrigation, water supply and hydroelectric power generation.
</P>
<P>
The dry season of the river has become longer as a result of
the arid climate, diversion of water for industrial and
agricultural purposes and the lack of a major water
reservoir. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971028.0095 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Research on Digestive System Highlighted in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Medical Association
launched a symposium in Beijing today on the research and
treatment of diseases of the digestive system.
</P>
<P>
The four-day event, the first of its kind in China, has
attracted 1,500 delegates from all parts of the country and more
than 50 experts from the United States, Germany, Japan and six
other countries.
</P>
<P>
Some 15 Chinese and 10 foreign scholars will give lectures on
the hot issues concerning research on digestive tract ailments,
and about 1,400 scientific theses will be circulated during the
meetings.
</P>
<P>
An exhibition of medical equipment and medicine and
demonstrations of advanced medical technology will also be held in
conjunction with the symposium. 
</P>
