<HEADLINE> Guizhou Starts to Build New Highway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, October 28 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guizhou Province
today began construction on its third high-quality highway to link
Guiyang, the provincial capital city, with Xinzhai, a small town
on the border of the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The project, which is scheduled to be completed by 2000, will
be partly financed by the Overseas Economic Cooperation Fund of
Japan, according to Lu Wanli, director of the provincial
administration for communications.
</P>
<P>
The road will be 260 km in length and is the largest of its
kind in the province.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Governor of the Province Wang Guangxian spoke at today's
opening ceremony, saying that the project will serve to improve
the traffic conditions of the province as well as the entire
southern region. 
