percent from the Dow Jones industrial average on Monday and
forced the New York Stock Exchange to halt trading.
</P>
<P>
The Washington Post:
</P>
<P>
-- Jiang Zemin, the leader of the world's most populous
nation, was feeling elated, and overwhelmed with the hospitality
of the tropical island state of Hawaii. He joined students from
a local hula dancing school for a three-minute impromptu session
of free-form undulation.
</P>
<P>
