<HEADLINE> "Italy Today" Exhibition to Be Held in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 28 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition titled "Italy
Today" will be held from November 25 to December 2 in Beijing at
the China International Exhibition Center, Italian sources
announced today.
</P>
<P>
They said at a press conference held today in Guangzhou,
capital city of south China's Guangdong Province, that the
exhibition will be the first of its kind sponsored in China by the
Italian government.
</P>
<P>
The show will be the most important trade-promotion activity
conducted by the Italian government in China over a decade, and
will be a milestone marking the economic and trade cooperation
between Italy and China, E. Bevilacqua, a senior Italian trade
official stationed in Beijing, said at the press conference.
</P>
<P>
Some 260 Italian companies, which are engaged in energy,
machinery, telecommunications, chemical industry, transport,
building materials, decoration, clothing and food, will
participate in the event, bringing with them the newest products
and equipment.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is expected to help the Chinese understanding
more about Italy, and offer an opportunity for more cooperation
between enterpreneurs in both countries, China's Minister of
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation Wu Yi said recently.
</P>
<P>
Italy is one of China's major economic and trading partners in
the European Union. Trade volume between the two countries in 1996
was nearly 5.1 billion US dollars. Italian businessmen have
invested about one billion US dollars in China. 
</P>
