<HEADLINE> Four More Coup Plotters Arrested in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Four more coup plotters in
Zambia have been arrested at the Mass Media Complex which houses
the Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation (ZNBC) and Zambia
News Agency, local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
The four men were caught at about 12:50 local time in the
continued search for more army rebels who were behind the
attempted coup early this morning, the state-run Zambia News
Agency said.
</P>
<P>
"We have just caught four more. One was found hiding in the
bush while the other three were found in the guardroom," one
officer was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Another person was caught at about 11:00 hours behind the ZNBC
studios hiding in an empty container.
</P>
<P>
The news agency quoted army sources as saying that at least
one soldier who tried to sneak away from the complex was shot
dead.
</P>
<P>
The search continues around the Mass Media Complex and general
atmosphere is still tense.
</P>
<P>
Army Commander General Nobby Simbeye already confirmed this
morning the arrests of a captain and five other soldiers.
</P>
