<HEADLINE> Iran Reiterates Support for Lebanon's Resistance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Iranian leader Ali Khamenei
today reiterated Tehran's support for the Lebanese resistance
movement against the Israeli occupation.
</P>
<P>
Receiving visiting Lebanese Prime Minister Rafik Hariri here,
Khamenei termed Lebanon as "the hero of Arab world" for its strong
resistance against Israel.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei lauded the Lebanese government for its "positive
attitude towards and support for the Lebanese resistance
movement."
</P>
<P>
South Lebanon is the last Arab-Israeli battle field. The
Iran-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God, is leading a guerrilla war
to oust Israelis from the 1,000-square-kilometer security zone
Israel set up in 1985 to prevent cross-border attacks.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Hariri said that expansion of relations between
Lebanon and Iran in all fields was very important for his
country.
</P>
<P>
Hariri arrived here Saturday for a four-day official visit,
the first by a Lebanese prime minister since Iran's Islamic
Revolution in 1979. He wound up his visit today and left for
Beirut.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Iran, Hariri held talks with Iranian
President Mohammad Khatami, First Vice President Hassan Habibi and
other senior Iranian officials. The two countries also signed
several cooperation agreements during Hariri's visit. 
