<HEADLINE> Cautiously Boosting Share-holding System: NPC Deputies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 28 (Xinhua) -- China's high-level legislators
today warned against indiscriminate development of the
share-holding system in China.
</P>
<P>
They urged a healthy and orderly endeavor for stock reform
during a bimonthly meeting attended by the members of the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC).
</P>
<P>
"The kind of collective economy that features, in the main, the
association of laborers in labor and their association in capital,
including the joint stock cooperative system, is also part of the
public ownership," said Li Yining, a member of the NPC Standing
Committee.
</P>
<P>
"Any business must not force all workers or farmers to buy
stocks during the process of standardizing the share-holding
system in China," said Li, a well-known economics professor at
Beijing University.
</P>
<P>
Those inefficient businesses should not be allowed to float
shares, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Xu Jing also called for effective measures to ensure smooth
development.
</P>
<P>
"Particularly the large businesses with sound high-tech
strength should pay enough attention to the negative effect
resulting from indiscreet mergers," Xu said.
</P>
<P>
Wu Shuqing said, "While issuing stocks, all companies should
pay more attention to effective running of the capital and the
transformation of management mechanism inside businesses."
</P>
<P>
He also stressed the necessity of separating the functions of
government from that of enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
