<HEADLINE> Tokyo Stocks Plunge to Lowest Level Since July 1995 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Tokyo stocks plunged today to
their lowest level in two years as traders rushed to sell issues
following the worst-ever point loss on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The key Nikkei average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange plunged 725.67 points or 4.26
percent to 16,312.69, the lowest since July 1995.
</P>
<P>
The Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), which covers all issues on
the First Section, fell 49.34 points or 3.76 percent to 1,263.11.
</P>
<P>
Volume on the First Section went up to 370 million shares today
from Monday's 317.14 million shares.
</P>
<P>
The largest single-day loss of more than 550 points in the
30-issue Dow Jones Industrial Average jolted the Tokyo and other
stock markets in Asia.
</P>
<P>
On the Tokyo Foreign Exchange, the U.S. dollar briefly dived to
the 119-yen level today in reaction to the overnight point fall on
Wall Street. 
</P>
