<HEADLINE> Swiss Consul Reiterates Confidence in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 28 (Xinhua) -- A senior Swiss envoy
announced today that a spectacular month-long promotion entitled
"Switzerland Greets Hong Kong" would take place here next month,
noting that his country wants to reiterate its confidence in
today's Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a news conference today, Swiss Consul General to
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) of China Rolf
Bodenmuller said that the SAR and Switzerland "have had good
relations over the years and economic links continue to develop."
</P>
<P>
With Hong Kong's return to its motherland, "we want to visibly
reiterate our confidence in the SAR while also giving the SAR
people a first hand opportunity to experience the diversity of
what our country offers," he said.
</P>
<P>
According to Bodenmuller, the "Switzerland Greets Hong Kong"
weeks will encompass a diverse range of cultural, entertainment
and economic activities, with an aim to bring Switzerland and its
many faces nearer to the SAR people and to get them more
interested in Switzerland well-known for its watches and tourist
paradises.
</P>
<P>
An Economic Forum on November 13 is one of the key events in
this upcoming diverse promotion.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland is the sixth largest foreign investor in Hong Kong.
The SAR is the eighth most important destination for Swiss exports
world-wide and the most important place in the world for exports
of Swiss watches. Switzerland is also a leading market for Hong
Kong products, with exports totaling 491 million U.S. dollars in
the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
There are about 1,500 Swiss citizens residing in Hong Kong,
making it the second biggest Swiss community in Asia. Furthermore,
over 150 subsidiaries or branches of Swiss enterprises, banks,
insurance companies and trading firms are present here.
</P>
<P>
The Swiss consul general told the news conference that "there
is a real and flourishing partnership between Switzerland and Hong
Kong, and there is definitely room to develop it."
</P>
<P>
"With our Swiss weeks, we want to underline that we strongly
believe in a prosperous future for Hong Kong and that the
confidence of the Swiss government and the Swiss business
community in this regard is very high," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
