<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Airport, World's 18th Most Satisfactory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The Macao International Airport
is the 18th most satisfactory among 39 world airports in a recent
survey, the Macao Daily News reported.
</P>
<P>
The airport ranks third in Asia after Singapore and Osaka
airports, the report quoted the Business Travel magazine as
saying. Hong Kong's Kai Tak Airport ranks 26th in the survey.
</P>
<P>
The survey was conducted among 730 passengers who travel at
least 28 times by air a year and whose annual income reach 110,000
U.S. dollars on average, it said.
</P>
<P>
The Macao airport got high points in its outlook and
convenience design, both ranking 10th. But it ranks only 19th in
the means of public transportation and 18th in handling
immigration (customs) procedure.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the airport also needs to improve its catering
service, which ranks 27th, and duty-free shop service, which ranks
 24th.
</P>
<P>
A similar survey conducted last year put Macao airport at 36th
among 45 world airports.
</P>
<P>
Inaugurated in November 1995, the Macao airport has opened
dozens of air routes to destinations in China's inland, Taiwan,
Southeast Asia and Europe.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
