<HEADLINE> Manila to Host ASEAN Meeting on Transnational Crimes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Officials from the nine-member
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) will meet here on
December 17-21 to explore ways of checking transnational crimes in
the region.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will consider and adopt measures to effectively
address the problems of illegal drug trafficking, arms smuggling
and money laundering in the region, the Philippine News Agency
reported today, quoting officials of the Philippine Foreign
Affairs Department.
</P>
<P>
The anti-crime meeting was endorsed by the first session of the
31st ASEAN Standing Committee held here early this month.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN groups Brunei, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar, the
Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam.  
</P>
