<HEADLINE> Asia Pacific Flooring Exhibition Opens in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The second Asia Pacific
Flooring Exhibition (Asiaflor) opened today at the Hong Kong
Convention and Exhibition Center, attracting 220 exhibitors from
all over the world.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony, Mike Chappell, director of the
 Britain-based company of Paragon Exhibition, which organizes
Asiaflor, said that he believes the Asia-Pacific region offers
very exciting business prospects not to be missed.
</P>
<P>
"For this reason Hong Kong was chosen as the ideal location for
Asiaflor, through which exhibitors are given the chance to tap the
opportunities of the region and to cater to the demand created by
the rapid development and volume of construction taking place in
this part of the world," Chappell said.
</P>
<P>
Asiaflor was first held in 1996 with over 160 exhibitors, but
the number of exhibitors rose more than 30 percent this year.
</P>
<P>
During the three-day show, exhibitors will showcase the full
range of flooring products for the commercial and residential
markets, as well as manufacturing and installation systems.
</P>
<P>
Compared with last year's show, wood and wood laminate
exhibitors have more than doubled and raw material and
technology-related exhibitors have trebled, which confirms
Asiaflor's importance for designers, specifiers and the flooring
trade.
</P>
<P>
Textiles such as carpets, rugs, tiles, entrance matting and
automotive carpets, are shown by many exhibitors, some showing
their products and designs for the first time in Asia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
