<HEADLINE> Swiss Envoy Believes HK's Dollar Link Will Not Change </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Swiss Consul General in the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) of China Rolf
Bodenmuller said today that he has a strong confidence in the
economic future of the SAR, believing that the Hong Kong Dollar's
link with the U.S. dollar will not change under the current
pressure from speculators.
</P>
<P>
After a news conference underlining next month's "Switzerland
Greets Hong Kong" promotion activities, Bodenmuller told Xinhua
that the current stock market turmoil has involved not only Hong
Kong, but also other regions or countries in Southeast Asia and
other parts of the world.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that he believes that Hong Kong, backed by the
motherland, is strong enough to face the current financial
challenge and that the SAR would not change its currency's link
with the U.S. dollar. In the recent days, the Hong Kong dollar has
been the top target of speculators' attack.
</P>
<P>
The Swiss envoy cited the SAR's Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa
and Financial Secretary Donald Tsang as saying that Hong Kong's
economy remains strong and steady and its finance not weak.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that "with our Swiss weeks (the "Switzerland
Greets Hong Kong" promotion), we want to underline that we
strongly believe in a prosperous future for Hong Kong and that the
confidence of the Swiss government and the Swiss business
community in this regard is very high." 
</P>
</TEXT>
