<HEADLINE> World Peace and Development Hopeful: Premier Li Peng </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 28 (Xinhua) -- For a long time to come it will
be possible to avert a new world war, Chinese Premier Li Peng
said, increasing hopes for world peace and development.
</P>
<P>
Li made the statement on October 17 in an interview with Salama
Ahmed Salama, acting editor-in-chief of the Egyptian newspaper
"Al-Ahram".
</P>
<P>
Noting that peace and development are still the main themes of
the present era, Li said that the international situation is
becoming more relaxed. He added that the trend toward
multipolarity has further developed globally in the political,
economic and other fields, which will benefit world peace,
stability and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the call of the people of all countries for
treating each other on an equal footing and living together
amicably is becoming louder and louder, and that it has become the
mainstream of the times to desire peace, seek cooperation and
promote development.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese people are devoting themselves to building
socialism with Chinese characteristics, he said, and that China's
goal is to completely modernize in the mid-21st century, so as to
build itself into a prosperous, strong, democratic, culturally
advanced socialist country.
</P>
<P>
China needs a longstanding, stable and peaceful international
environment, especially a surrounding environment of
good-neighborliness, to concentrate on advancing economy and
raising people's standards of living, the Chinese premier said.
</P>
<P>
China's sustained and rapid economic growth has benefited from
a stable and tranquil regional environment since the beginning of
its reform and opening-up policies 19 years ago, Li said, and
China's economic advancement and prosperity has contributed to
promoting stability and prosperity in the region.
</P>
<P>
China will continue to work for regional peace and development,
and to fulfill its due responsibilities and obligation, Li said,
noting that a stable, developing and strong China will not pose a
threat to any other countries, but will make an even greater
contribution to peace and development in Asia and in the world as
a whole. 
</P>
</TEXT>
