<HEADLINE> Li Peng on Sino-Egyptian Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 28 (Xinhua) -- China has all along regarded
Egypt as its important partner in the Arab world as well as in
Africa, and China is ready to work with Egypt, in the spirit of
mutual respect and benefit, and equality, to bring a friendly
bilateral cooperation to the 21st century, Chinese premier Li Peng
has said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese leader made the remarks in an interview with Salama
Ahmed Salama, acting editor-in-chief and first editor of the
Egyptian newspaper "Al-Ahram", in Beijing on October 17.
</P>
<P>
China and Egypt have enjoyed friendly relations based on mutual
understanding and respect, although great changes have taken place
in the world over the past decades, the Chinese premier noted.
</P>
<P>
In the 1990s, Li said, bilateral relations have scored some new
development, as both sides not only have continued to support each
other and maintain close cooperation in international affairs, but
also forged mutually beneficial ties of cooperation in the fields
of politics, economy, trade, agriculture, science, technology and
culture.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, China and Egypt have seen fruitful cooperation
in culture, sports, education and science and technology, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Through joint efforts by the two sides, bilateral trade and
economic cooperation, as an important part of Sino-Egyptian
friendly relations, has maintained a stable and sustainable
development, with a trade volume exceeding 400 million US dollars
last year, he said.
</P>
<P>
There are great potential and broad prospects for further
expansion of Sino-Egyptian trade and economic cooperation, he
added.
</P>
<P>
The premier suggested the two governments encourage more
exchanges and understanding between businesses of the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
He said he believes mutually beneficial cooperation through
various forms and at various levels will expand increasingly.
</P>
<P>
According to a memorandum of understanding, signed during
Egyptian Prime Minister Kamal Ahmed El-Ganzouri's China visit in
April this year, China will help Egypt establish a free trade zone
in northern Suez.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Government attaches great importance to this
project, he said, adding that China's relevant departments have
submitted a report to the Egyptian side, and China is looking
forward to an early reply from the Egyptian side for the sake of
future cooperation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
