<HEADLINE> China to Work for Middle East Peace: Premier Li Peng </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government highly
values its traditional friendship with Arab nations and supports
their rights and interests and Egypt's positive efforts and
important role in the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
China will, together with the international community, continue
to make an unremitting efforts to advance the peace process.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Li Peng made the statements in a recent
interview with Salama Ahmed Salama, acting editor-in-chief of the
Egyptian newspaper "Al-Ahram."
</P>
<P>
Li said that Egypt initiated the Middle East peace process, and
has made major contributions in seeking a comprehensive and just
peace in the region, thereby winning admiration from the
international community.
</P>
<P>
Major progress had been made in the peace process through the
efforts of the international community and all parties concerned,
Li said. "We are concerned about the current impasse of the peace
process."
</P>
<P>
Only after a comprehensive and just peace is realized, all
nations in the region can enjoy real security, he said. The
realization of peace will not only serve interests of the region,
but will also benefit world peace and development, Li added.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that all parties concerned will oppose interference
and remove obstacles to restore peace negotiations at an early
date on the basis of the relevant resolutions of the United
Nations and 'land for peace' principles, so as to push ahead the
peace process and finally achieve regional peace, stability and
development," Premier Li said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Chinese government has supported solidarity
and cooperation among the gulf nations, and is opposed to external
threats and interference. China holds that remaining problems
should be settled in a just and reasonable way, based on the
relevant resolutions of the U.N. Security Council.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the delayed solution of the remaining problems
from the Gulf War will not be helpful to regional peace and
development, or comply with the desire of the relevant nations to
improve relations and cause their national economies to prosper.
</P>
<P>
China values friendship with the gulf nations, and is ready to
advance friendly and cooperative ties with them in a variety of
areas, Li said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
