<HEADLINE> Premier on Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 28 (Xinhua) -- China has required governments
at all level to be responsible for environmental protection and
earnestly carry out a strategy of sustainable development, Chinese
Premier Li Peng said.
Y  Li made the remarks in an interview with Salama Ahmed Salama,
acting editor-in-chief and first editor of the Egyptian newspaper
"Al-Ahram" on October 17.
</P>
<P>
He said China has viewed environmental protection as a matter
of overall importance, and has taken protecting the environment as
a basic national policy since it initiated the policy of reforms
and opening-up.
</P>
<P>
China has formulated a series of policies and laws to step up
environmental protection, Li said, adding that in 1996 China had
shut down 60,000 small businesses which were severe polluters.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the country's 9 percent economic growth rate since
1979 has generally not damaged the environment because of the
effectiveness of protective measures.
</P>
<P>
China has incorporated sustainable development into its
strategy for modernization in accordance with the Ninth Five-year
Plan for National Economic and Social Development and the
Long-Range Objectives to the Year 2010 adopted in the fourth
Session of the Eighth National People's Congress held in March
last year, Li said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
