<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Says Mong Cai Becomes Prosperity Gateway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Mong Cai, a small town bordering
China is rapidly becoming a prosperity gateway of Vietnam, the
Vietnam News reported today.
</P>
<P>
Infrastructure construction, cross-border tourism, trading,
services and investment activities have changed the face of this
northern town of Vietnam's Quang Ninh Province as it cashed in on
the growing bilateral trade between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
"Each year, some 100 billion Vietnamese dong (about 8.3
U.S. dollars) has been spent on infrastructure with at least 60
percent raised from local residents," said the people's committee
chairman of Hai Ninh District, Tran Khac Ky.
</P>
<P>
In the first nine months of this year, 379,879 Chinese and
263,012 Vietnamese crossed the border to Mong Cai or to its sister
town of Dong Xing on the Chinese side for trade purpose.
</P>
<P>
More than 86,000 Chinese came to visit Mong Cai's tourism
attraction Tra Co Beach, said the Vietnam News. 
</P>
