<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier On China's Economic, Political Reforms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 28 (Xinhua) -- China will continue its
political restructuring along with its increasing economic
restructuring, Chinese Premier Li Peng has said.
</P>
<P>
Li made the statement in an October 17 interview with Salama
Ahmed Salama, acting editor-in-chief and first editor of Egypt's
"Al-Ahram" newspaper, in Beijing, where Premier Li explained the
main tasks of political restructuring.
</P>
<P>
The main tasks are: developing democracy, improving the legal
system, separating government functions from enterprise
management, streamlining administrative structure, improving the
democratic supervisory system, and safeguarding stability and
unity.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the recent 15th National Party Congress designated
Deng Xiaoping Theory as the Party guideline and people should
adhere to the reform orientation of the socialist market economy to
bring new breakthroughs in the reform.
</P>
<P>
This mainly includes: readjusting and improving the ownership
structure; developing the economy of diverse forms of ownership
while keeping public ownership in a dominant position;
accelerating the reform of state-owned enterprises and
establishing a modern enterprise system; improving the structure
and modes of distribution, but keeping the distribution according
to work in a dominant position, but with a variety of modes of
distribution.
</P>
<P>
It also includes bringing into full play the rile of the market
mechanism and improving macroeconomic control system;
strengthening agriculture's role as the foundation of the economy,
and readjusting and optimizing the economic structure;
implementing the strategy of development through science,
tehcnology and education and achieving sustainable development;
and striving to do better in opening-up to the outside world and
making an active, rational and effective use of overseas funds.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
