<DOCNO> XIE19971028.0159 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Can Overcome Unhealthy Tendencies of Market Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 28 (Xinhua) -- China is now in a period of
economic structural shifting from the old to a new, and the
shifting is affected by many domestic and foreign factors, and
money worship, corruption, and other crimes are cropping up in the
social and economic life of China, Chinese premier Li Peng said,
but he added: "We are able and have the means to solve these
problems."
</P>
<P>
The Chinese leader said this while responding to a question by
Salama Ahmed Salama, acting editor-in-chief and the first editor
of the Egyptian newspaper "Al-Ahram" on October 17.
</P>
<P>
Li named three ways of solving the problems:
</P>
<P>
The first is to promote socialist ethical and cultural
progress, improve the quality of the entire nation, and guide
people to foster a correct world outlook, outlook on life and
concept of value.
</P>
<P>
The second is to continue the reforms to remove the soil that
corruption grows in.
</P>
<P>
The third is to promote the development of democracy and the
legal system, improve the democratic supervisory system, and
prevent the abuse of power.
</P>
<P>
There must be laws to abide by and everyone must obey the
law. Laws must be enforced strictly and law-breakers must be
brought to book, he said, adding that those whose duty is law
enforcement but break the law and take bribes and bend the law
must be punished severely.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that market economy does not belong just to
capitalism, and that socialism can also adopt a market
economy. China's economic reforms are aimed at establishing a
system of a socialist market economy, and any form of management
or organization that reflects the rules of socialized production
can be used.
</P>
<P>
"Our guideline is to maintain public ownership as the mainstay
while securing common development of all sectors of the economy,"
he said, adding that further readjusting and improving the
structure of ownership is a major task of economic reform.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the non-public sectors have grown remarkably and
have become an important part of the socialist economy, and
encouraging these sectors to expand in a healthy way is important
for meeting market demands, increasing employment, and developing
productivity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
