<HEADLINE> Turkish Foreign Minister Ends Visit to Macedonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Foreign Minister Ismail
Cem ended his two-day official visit to Macedonia today.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Cem held talks with his Macedonian
counterpart Blagoj Handziski on bilateral relations and the
situation in the Balkan region.
</P>
<P>
The two sides signed an agreement on cooperation between their
foreign ministries, and a memorandum on trade and textile
production.
</P>
