joint investment and bilateral cooperation agreements, which had
been ratified by the two governments.
</P>
<P>
Cem, who also met with Macedonian President Kiro Gligorov,
President of the Assembly Tito Petkovsk and Prime Minister Branko
Crvenkovski, left for Albania today. 
