<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Shares Down 7 Percent in Early Trading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 28 (Xinhua) -- German share values plunged over
seven percent in early trading today in reaction to Wall Street's
dramatic losses on Monday, said reports reaching here from
Frankfurt.
</P>
<P>
The main 30-share Dax index was quoted at 3,600 points just
after opening, down 279.12 points from Monday's closing of
3,879.12.
</P>
<P>
Traders are waiting to see what would happen next on the New
York market.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, the U.S. dollar opened today at 1.7285-1.7290
marks, compared with Monday's official median rate of 1.7650 marks.
</P>
<P>
Following a 550-point loss on New York exchanges, the worst
crash in 10 years there, Hong Kong stock market saw a nosedive of
13 percent in early trading, with the Hang Seng index down 1,362
points to 9,136 one and a half hours after opening.
</P>
<P>
Last Thursday, the Hong Kong market dropped 10 percent and had
triggered off selling across the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
