<HEADLINE> Bank of Italy Reserves Reach 130 Trillion Lire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 27 (Xinhua) -- The reserves of the Bank of Italy
broke the threshold of 130 trillion lire (more than 75 billion
U.S. dollars) in September and hit a new record high.
</P>
<P>
The Italian Exchange Office said that at the end of September
the central bank's reserves amounted to 130.796 trillion lire.
</P>
