<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-Indonesian Cooperation Benefits Peace in Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian Defense and Security
Minister Edi Sudrajat said here today that cooperation in various
fields between China and Indonesia is very important for the
preservation of peace and stability in the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
When meeting with visiting Chinese Air Force Commander Liu
Shunyao, Sudrajat expressed his satisfaction over the development
of the relations between Indonesia and China and their armies.
</P>
<P>
Some countries in Asia-Pacific belong to developing countries
and they can not develop their economy and raise the living
standard of their people without a peaceful and stable
international environment, the minister noted.
</P>
<P>
Sudrajat, who had just finished a visit to China, said that
China is devoted to economic development and raising the living
standard of its people.
</P>
<P>
He held that China's political situation is stable and believed
that China's economy will develop at high speed.
</P>
<P>
Liu Shunyao, who arrived here on October 23 for a one-week
visit, expressed his satisfaction with the result of his visit,
saying it has reached the goal of strengthening understanding,
learning from each other and developing friendship between the two
sides.
</P>
<P>
On October 24, Liu met with Commander of Indonesian Armed
Forces General Feisal Tanjung and Air Force Chief of Staff Air
Marshal Sutria Tubagus.
</P>
<P>
Liu and his party will leave here Wednesday for Malaysia.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
