<DOCNO> XIE19971028.0192 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Finance Chief: HK Stock Setback Temporary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Philippine Finance Secretary
Roberto de Ocampo said the Hong Kong economy is "fundamentally
strong" and the Hong Kong stock market is expected to bounce back
soon.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine News Agency today quoted the finance chief as
saying that the current situation being faced by Hong Kong further
reinforces the view that strong economic fundamentals are an
important element in weathering this passing storm in the region.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few days, the Hong Kong stock market has joined
other markets in the region in sharp declines as a result of the
"contagion effect" of the currency crisis sweeping Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
After tumbling 646 points Monday in the market's worst slide in
8 years, Hong Kong's 33-stock Hang Seng Index fell as much as
1,621.80 points to 8876 at today's intra-day trading.
</P>
<P>
However, Hong Kong's economy is "fundamentally strong" and is
thus expected to quickly weather the financial storm which has
been hitting Southeast Asian nations since July, de Ocampo said.
</P>
<P>
He also appealed to investors to keep calm, saying that the
financial crisis in Asia is just "a temporary setback" and that
Asian economies will recover from the crisis "stronger than
before."
</P>
<P>
"There is no need to panic", he said, noting that the fall in
Asian stock markets is "a corrective action rather than a
long-term trend".
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
