<DOCNO> XIE19971028.0196 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Africa Military to Return Land to Civilians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 28 (Xinhua) -- South Africa has decided
to return large tracts of land held by the military to civilian
use, local daily the Citizen reported today.
</P>
<P>
The plan was approved by the cabinet last week and announced
in Pretoria Monday, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The Department of Defense reportedly holds about 482,000
hectares of land.
</P>
<P>
Defense Minister Joe Modise said Monday that the reason for
the return of military land to civilians was that the defense
force was beginning to shrink.
</P>
<P>
"We are releasing land because we think there is a need for us
to do so," he said.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, it was too early to say how much of this
land his department would relingquish. He said some would be
retained for military purposes, including battle schools and
firing ranges.
</P>
<P>
The defense forces has since 1986 retunred about 234,000
hectares of land to the Department of Public Works. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
