<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Norway Aids Mozambique in Rural Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The Norwegian government is to
donate 1.7 million U.S. Dollars to help boost the rural economy
in the southeastern African country.
</P>
<P>
Local paper, Noticias, said today that an agreement was signed
between the governments of Mozambique and Norway Monday.
</P>
<P>
The aid is to help farmers resume production and develop their
economy, according to the agreement signed.
</P>
<P>
The Norwegian government is also to help raise the efficiency
of the grass-root governments and better plan their development
micro-economy strategy for a sustained development, the agreement
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
