<DOCNO> XIE19971028.0198 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambian President Says Coup Crushed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Zambian President Frederick
Chiluba said in a radio broadcast today that a planned coup had
been crushed and he was back in control.
</P>
<P>
"I am happy to announce that the plans of our enemies have been
thwarted," the president said.
</P>
<P>
"Their plans have failed and my government is still firmly in
control. I want to warn those who want to rise that they will fall
by the sword," he said about five hours after a group calling
itself the National Redemption Council announced it had seized
power.
</P>
<P>
"The enemy is defeated. Victory is ours in Jesus name," he said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today soldiers led by a man calling himself Captain
Solo announced the coup through Zambia News Broadcasting
Corporation.
</P>
<P>
The number of soldiers involved in the coup was not known. It
was reported that some those responsible had been arrested.
</P>
<P>
"We have arrested the coup plotters and will make many more
arrests as investigation go on," a senior advisor to Chiluba was
quoted as saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
