<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Signs Covenant on Economic, Social, Cultural Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Ambassador to
the United Nations Qin Huasun, on behalf of the Chinese
government, today signed the International Covenant on Economic,
Social and Cultural Rights.
</P>
<P>
At the signing ceremony, Qin said this was a significant action
taken by the Chinese government after serious consideration, and
it manifested again China's firm commitment to the promotion of
the human rights both in the country and the world at large.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Qin, on the behalf of the Chinese government,
declared that the signature that the Taiwan authorities affixed,
by using the name of "China", to this covenant on October 5, 1967,
was illegal, and null and void.
</P>
<P>
The International Covenant on Economic, Social and Cultural
Rights was adopted by the U.N. General Assembly in 1966. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
