<DOCNO> XIE19971028.0201 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tourist Arrivals to Philippines Reach 1.4 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Visitor arrivals in the
Philippines reached 1.41 million for the first eight months this
year, an increase of 10.5 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
A report released by the Philippines' Department of Tourism
today said the largest number of arrivals was recorded in July
with a total of 187,000. But June posted the highest growth rate
of 18.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The report said that East Asia remained the top contributor of
tourists to the Philippines. Some 36,400 Japanese tourists came to
the country during the period.
</P>
<P>
Other top contributors include the United States, South Korea,
Hong Kong, Britain, Australia, Germany, Canada, France and some
Southeast Asian nations, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the country's tourist arrivals broke the 2-million
mark for the first time, posting the highest growth rate of 16.6
percent in Asia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
