<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0730 GMT, October 28 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA -- A military coup against President Frederick Chiluba
was confirmed by Zambian state radio Tuesday morning.
</P>
<P>
The radio said the chiefs of the army and police had been
sacked and the airport had been closed. Gunfire of small arms and
cannons have been heard from the general direction of Zambia's
state house.
</P>
<P>
A group calling itself the National Redemption Council, headed
by a captain Solo, was claiming to have carried out the coup.
(Zambia-coup)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WILLIAMSBURG, Virginia -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin arrived
Monday night at Langley military base near Williamsburg, the
second stop of his nine-day state visit to the United States.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who started the visit on Sunday, arrived here after a
stopover in Honolulu, Hawaii. (U.S.-Jiang-Visit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Lithuania opposes "a hasty refusal" of the security
guarantee proposal made by Russian President Boris Yeltsin to the
three Baltic nations.
</P>
<P>
Lithuanian President Algirdas Brazauskas said Monday at a press
conference in Vilnius, Capital of Lithuania, that the Baltic
nations had refused Yeltsin's proposal "too hastily", though they
could express their ideas on this issue after careful
deliberations, according to reports reaching here.
(Russia-Baltics-Security)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BUDAPEST -- The Bank of China (BOC) opened its office in
Budapest Monday, the first Chinese financial institution in
Eastern Europe.
</P>
<P>
The office will carry out information exchanges with Hungarian
financial circles and prepare for the setting-up of a network
between the BOC and its branches in Eastern Europe, bank officials
said. (Hungary-China-Bank)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KIEV -- Delegates of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization
(NATO)'s political committee arrived here Monday for a two-day
visit.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, which is the first of its kind to visit Ukraine
since the two sides signed the Special Partnership Charter in
July, is expected to discuss with the country the development of
Ukrainian-NATO cooperation and the implementation of the Special
Partnership Charter. (Ukraine-NATO-Cooperation) 
</P>
</TEXT>
