<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Coup Makers Besiege Zambia's State House </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Situation in Zambia's capital
is unclear so far with some sporadic shots heard in the urban
area after an on-going coup staged by the army.
</P>
<P>
All government offices and shops are closed this morning and
except the armored vehicles and military vehicles with soldiers,
few cars and people can be seen in the streets.
</P>
<P>
Soldiers led by Captain Solo (only name) who announced the
coup at seven o'clock local time through Zambia News Broadcasting
Corporation are still surrounding the State House, where
President Frederick Chiluba lives, and the buildings of Zambia
News Agency have been captured by anti-government soldiers.
</P>
<P>
The statement made by the coup leader said Chiluba must
surrender at nine o'clock local time and leave the state house or
the presidency will be taken by force.
</P>
<P>
The number of soldiers involved in the coup is not available.
</P>
<P>
However, an army officer at the Ministry of Defense told
Xinhua on condition of anonymity that soldiers supporting the
government in other provinces are marching toward the capital.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
