<HEADLINE> Philippine High-level Military Delegation Visits Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's Deputy Prime Minister
and Foreign Minister Nguyen Manh Cam said that military
co-operation between Vietnam and the Philippines was indispensable
because both nations are members of the Association of Southeast
Asian Nations (ASEAN), local newspapers said today.
</P>
<P>
Cam made the remarks Monday during a meeting with a high-level
military delegation of the Philippines led by Chief of the General
Staff, General Arnulfo G. Acedera Jr., which began its Vietnam
tour last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
General Acedera Jr. said he was happy with the results of talks
with his Vietnamese counterpart and hoped to strengthen the
relations between the two armies.
</P>
<P>
Cam welcomed the Philippine military visit to Vietnam,
describing it as a good opportunity for both sides to enhance
mutual understanding.
</P>
<P>
He said he hoped that the two armies would conduct regular
exchanges of visits, thus boosting their friendly relationship,
contributing to developing the relationship between Vietnam and
the Philippines in the common development of the ASEAN group.
</P>
<P>
The visiting Philippine military delegation was also received
by Vietnam's National Defense Minister Pham Van Tra Monday.
</P>
<P>
Tra highly appreciated the delegation's visit, which he said
contributed to promoting the relations between the two armies and
the general staffs in particular. 
</P>
</TEXT>
