<DOCNO> XIE19971028.0211 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Investment Ranks First at China's Three Gorges Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong investment has been
playing an important role in China's massive Three Gorges Water
Control Project at Yichang, Hubei Province, according to
Deputy-Mayor Zhang Jianyi.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong investors have put 940 million US dollars into 320
enterprises in Yichang, accounting for 70 percent of the
overseas-funded firms registered there, Zhang says.
</P>
<P>
In the first ten months of this year, the city brought in 100
million US dollars in overseas investment, 74 million of that from
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong investors are active in a number of businesses in the
industrial, transportation, hi-tech, and entertainment
sectors. The biggest overseas-backed joint venture in the city is
a Hong Kong-funded polyester chip project that cost 148 million US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The second phase of damming of the Yangtze River will need even
more investment, Zhang says, and the city has made Hong Kong
investment a priority item. Some well-known Hong Kong enterprises
like the Kerry Group, Sun Hung Kai Group, Henderson Group, and
Universal Group are showing interest in co-operating. 
</P>
</TEXT>
