<DOCNO> XIE19971028.0215 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing, HK Universities Join Hands in Traditional Medical Research </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Two Beijing-based universities
and one Hong Kong university will jointly launch a five-year
research program on traditional Chinese medicine.
</P>
<P>
Under a cooperation agreement, The studies done by Qinghua
University, the Beijing University of Traditional Chinese Medicine
and the Hong Kong Baptist University are expected to lead to new
cures in traditional medical procedures for cardiovascular and
cerebral diseases, cancer and immune system diseases, according to
Yang Jiaqing, vice-president of Qinghua.
</P>
<P>
Researchers hope their results can be used to develop drugs,
which after clinical testing will be available on both domestic
and foreign markets.  
</P>
</TEXT>
