<HEADLINE> Military Coup Confirmed by Zambian Radio </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, October 28 (Xinhua) -- A military coup against
President Frederick Chiluba was announced by Zambian state radio
this morning.
</P>
<P>
The radio said the chiefs of the army and police had been
sacked and the airport had been closed.
</P>
<P>
Gunfire of small arms and cannons have been heard from the
general direction of Zambia's state house.
</P>
<P>
A reliable source told Xinhua that Zambia's military medical
personnel had been informed to get ready.
</P>
<P>
A group calling itself the National Redemption Council, headed
by a captain Solo, was claiming to have carried out the coup and
had promised to issue a further statement later.
</P>
<P>
The coup leader said he was attempting to put an end to chaos
caused by crime and corruption in the country.
</P>
<P>
Earlier report by Radio Zambia said the state house had been
besieged. And the coupists have asked Chiluba to express his
attitude toward the coup before 8:00 am. 
</P>
</TEXT>
