<HEADLINE> Chinese President Arrives in Williamsburg </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WILLIAMSBURG, Virginia, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese
President Jiang Zemin arrived here tonight, the second stop of his
nine-day state visit to the United States.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's ongoing trip, at the invitation of President Bill
Clinton, marks the first by a Chinese head of state to the United
States in 12 years.
</P>
<P>
The president and his entourage were greeted at the airport by
Hampton Mayor Jimmy Eason, Williamsburg Mayor Gilbert Granger and
President of the Colonial Williamsburg Foundation Robert
C. Wilburn, as well as other local officials and senior army
officers.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday morning, Jiang will tour the Colonial Williamsburg,
which was reconstructed between 1926 to 1956. The town, which was
called Jamestown before 1699, served as the seat of government and
administrative center of England's largest colony in North America
after the first English adventurers set foot on Virginian soil in
the 17th century.
</P>
<P>
Jiang arrived here from Honolulu, Hawaii. After Williamsburg,
he will visit Washington D.C., New York, Boston and Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
In Washington, Jiang is to hold talks with President Clinton on
China-U.S. relations and major international issues of shared
interest. 
</P>
</TEXT>
