<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Produce 2000 MW Power More By 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Additional 2000 megawatts of
power will be produced in Bangladesh by the year 2000, which will
be more than the present demand of 3,150 mw, the independent
United News of Bangladesh (UNB) reported today.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed by Bangladeshi Power, Energy and Mineral
Resources Minister Mohammad Nuruddin Khan while visiting the site
of the 100-mw barge mounted power plant in Khulna District last
week.
</P>
<P>
Under the program, the minister said, 1,200 mw electricity will
be produced by private initiatives and 800 mw by the government.
</P>
<P>
The present government has been working hard to establish power
plants under public and private initiatives with a view to meeting
increasing demand, the minister stated.
</P>
<P>
Measures to set up barge-mounted power plants along with
land-based power centers within the shortest possible time in
private sector have also been taken considering the time-consuming
and expensive nature of power production, he added.
</P>
<P>
The minister also said that final agreements have been reached
with two companies and agreements with two others are afoot. He
hoped that production would begin within 10 months of the
agreements.  
</P>
</TEXT>
