<HEADLINE> Polish Press Enthusiastic About Jiang's U.S. Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Major Polish newspapers today
covered Chinese President Jiang Zemin's visit to the United States
and viewed it an important visit with "turning significance".
</P>
<P>
The Trybuna newspaper, the organ for Poland's Social Democratic
Party, said in a signed article that the whole world was paying
great attention to President Jiang's visit to the U.S. It was
regarded as the most important event during the recent few months
by commentators, even before Jiang started his trip.
</P>
<P>
China was one of the countries with the fastest economic
development and played an important role in the world. Chinese
economic reform was deepening and had achieved remarkable success.
</P>
<P>
As a result, China had experienced consecutive economic
increases averaging 10 percent yearly, and living conditions were
notably improved. These had greatly changed Washington's, and
other countries' attitudes towards China, the article said.
</P>
<P>
It wished the visit full success.
</P>
<P>
The Zycie Warszawy newspaper expressed belief in an article
that the visit would promote China to open more to the
world. Jiang's visit, which went beyond the category of bilateral
trade relations, would be an historic turning for
Sino-U.S. relations, it said.
</P>
<P>
Other popular newspapers, including the Rzeczpospolita and the
Gazeta Wyborcza newspapers, also gave prominent coverage to the
first visit to the U.S. by a Chinese leader in 12 years. It was a
major event in Sino-U.S. relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
