<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
suffered the biggest one-day slump since the 1987 crash with the
key indicator tumbling over 12 percent. The loss of share value
was estimated at 6 billion NZ dollars (3.66 billion US dollars).
