<HEADLINE> European Scientists to Cooperate in Research Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Scientists from 11 Central
European countries have recently decided to jointly undertake a
research project on geodynamics.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by the European Foundation for Sciences, researchers
will study the vertical and horizontal movement of the earth's
crust in a wide area ranging from the Carpathian Mts, the East
Alps to the Baltic Sea.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman from the Research Institute of Geometrics and
Geodynamics under the Academy of Engineering told reporters that
the project consisted of several regional programs, involving the
lowlands in Hungary, the highlands in the Czech Republic and the
frontier area of the Alps.
</P>
<P>
It intended to determine the movement of the earth's crust in
the central European continent by conducting regular measurement
in 30 selected spots.
</P>
<P>
Scientists conjectured that the Carpathian Mts was moving
northward at a low rate of 1-3 centimeters a year. Research
results from the project are expected to provide reliable
scientific evidence for the hypothesis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
