<HEADLINE> Over 486 kg Narcotic Drugs Seized in Myanmar in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, October 28 (Xinhua) -- A total of over 486 kilograms of
narcotic drugs, including 67 kilograms of heroin and 323.66
kilograms of opium and other kinds of narcotic drugs, were seized
by the Myanmar authorities in the country in September, the
official daily the Mirror reported today.
</P>
<P>
The seizure, made by the army units, police force and customs
departments, also included 61.1 liters of phensedyl, over 71
liters of acetic anhydride and other liquid chemicals, and 100,000
tablets of stimulant drug.
</P>
<P>
The Myanmar authorities took action against 412 people in 317
drug-related cases in the month, the report said.
</P>
<P>
In August, over 480 kilograms of narcotic drugs were
confiscated in the country, according to an earlier official
report.  
