<TEXT>
<P>
SANTA FE DE BOGOTA, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Colombia's ruling
Liberal Party obtained 20 of the 33 governorships in the country's
municipal elections concluded Sunday, preliminary results
indicated.
</P>
<P>
The Conservative Party got six governorships and the other
small parties won the remaining seven.
</P>
<P>
The elections ended without serious violence despite a few
clashes in which four guerrillas were killed and a soldier was
injured.
</P>
<P>
The polls were carried out in "relative normality," the
authorities said.
</P>
<P>
Over the last two months, the rebels launched a sabotage
campaign that saw dozens of candidates killed and hundreds
intimidated into withdrawing.
</P>
<P>
In a parallel voting, more than 9 million people condemned
violence in Colombia, which has left a death toll of 30,000 and
has forced a million people to leave their homeland.
</P>
<P>
The voting to peace was supported by 400 national and
international governmental and non-governmental organizations.
</P>
