<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment Increasing in North China Free Trade Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The Tianjin Free Trade Zone, in
this Chinese port city, used 570 million US dollars in foreign
capital in the first nine months, 26 percent more than for the
whole of 1996.
</P>
<P>
The six year-old zone has approved 3,000 foreign-backed
companies, with 3.6 billion US dollars in all, 2.4 billion dollars
of that from foreign investment. The foreign-funded companies
account for 80 percent of the zone's companies.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, the zone had 51 foreign-backed
projects worth two million US dollars each, and this year, another
31 similar agreements have been signed, nine of them valued at
more than 20 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Export-oriented processing is a fast growing business in the
zone, with 20 large or medium-sized ones that have a combined
investment of 200 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
A center backed by two Hong Kong companies and valued at 29.8
million US dollars, is being built.  
</P>
