<HEADLINE> PICC Wins BBB Credit Rating </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The People's Insurance Company
(Group) of China has received the BBB credit rating from the
Standard and Poor's Co., today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
The international credit rating organization also listed PICC
as the 20th largest insurance company in the world.
</P>
<P>
The BBB rating means that PICC was treated as an insurer with
adequate financial security and strong compensation ability to
meet the responsibility carried by its insurance policies, said a
company official.
</P>
<P>
The crediting rating was given by more than 100 insurance
analysts of Standard and Poor's which has collected information
about more than 4,000 insurance companies from 70 countries and
regions.
</P>
<P>
As the country's largest insurance company, PICC Group reported
a satisfying business record during the first nine months of the
year with its total insurance premium income increasing by 43.4
percent.
</P>
<P>
The group's insured property value during the past nine months
amounted to 6.96 trillion yuan (837.96 US dollars), making its
property insurance premium income rise by 10.85 percent from the
same period of last year.  
</P>
