stressed today that Yeltsin's proposal was "unacceptable" while
Lithuanian Parliament Chairman Vytautas Landsbergis said it had
rendered the three nations "protectorates."
</P>
<P>
Also, Estonian Foreign Ministry Spokesman Vaino Reinart said
Estonia, guided by the principle of "indivisibility of European
security," would not rely on the security guarantees offered
merely by an individual country. 
