<HEADLINE> Mexico's Trade Surplus $1.84 Billion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Mexico's foreign trade surplus
was 1.84 billion U.S. dollars in the first nine months of this
year, but imports grew faster than exports, the Finance
Secretariat said today.
</P>
<P>
Mexico exported 80.618 billion dollars of goods in
January-September, a 15.6 percent of increase over the same period
of 1996, the secretariat said.
</P>
<P>
However, Mexico imported 78.778 billion dollars worth of goods
in the nine months, 22.7 percent more than the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the first nine months of 1996, exports of
manufactured products jumped 18.1 percent to 68.814 billion dollars
in the same period this year, and exports of oil and oil products
earned 8.51 billion dollars for the country, a 2.7 percent rise.
</P>
</TEXT>
