<HEADLINE> Developing South China's Audiovisual Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 28 (Xinhua) -- A large audiovisual center
will open to business here on November 5 during the '97 China
Audiovisual Products Fair.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Ministry of Culture has decided to build four
wholesale audiovisual markets. The other three will be in Beijing,
Shanghai, and Wuhan.
</P>
<P>
The market has 180 wholesalers and has become the main source
of approved audiovisual products in the province. It sells about
17,000 varieties of audiovisual product, mainly VCDs, CDs, DVDs,
and video tapes from China and abroad.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Ministry of Culture and the Guangdong government
have stated that, with the opening of the market, wholesale
audiovisual product business will no longer be done elsewhere.
