<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Train Agricultural Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka has launched a
training program for agricultural workers in an effort to enhance
their agricultural knowledge and skills, a spokesman for the
Vocational Training and Rural Industry Ministry said here today.
</P>
<P>
Under the program, workers of each agricultural sector will
study how to plant and harvest their crops in a scientific way. In
training centers nationwide, they will also learn some practical
techniques in the production of tea, coconut, rubber and latex.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman attributed Sri Lanka's low-level productivity in
agriculture to the lack of know-how of those workers who are
reluctant to give up traditional production methods.
</P>
<P>
As part of the training program, workers will be provided with
some equipment, such as tree climbing gears, plucking tools and
coconut husking machines, at a fair price.  
</P>
