<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Damming of China's Yellow River Successful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAOLANGDI (Yellow River), October 28 (Xinhua) -- China's
Yellow River was fully blocked at 10:28 am today on a section
40 km north of Luoyang, an ancient capital of China in Henan
province.
</P>
<P>
The dam is the 12th on the river and marks the beginning of
the construction of the Xiaolangdi Multi-Purpose Water Control
Project. Its main purpose is to prevent the perennial flooding,
which has been referred to as the "sorrow of the Chinese nation".
</P>
<P>
The past 2,500 years of recorded history show that the river
has gone over its banks more than 1,500 times and has claimed the
lives of hundreds of thousands of people.
</P>
<P>
The water control project started in 1994 and is the second
largest after the Three Gorges Project on the Yangtze River in the
south.
</P>
<P>
Ninety-three percent of the Yellow River's
649,000-sq.-km. drainage area is located upstream from Xiaolangdi,
which is expected to increase the flood prevention capacity along
the river, allowing it to stop the kind of catastrophic floods
that happen every 1,000 years.
</P>
<P>
Premier Li Peng attended today's ceremony to celebrate the
success of the dam work, which took more than 40 hours to
complete.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971028.0268 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Premier Li Peng Hails Success of Yellow River Damming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAOLANGDI (YELLOW RIVER), October 28 (Xinhua) -- The join-up
of the dam on the Yellow River proved that the Xiaolangdi
Multi-Purpose Water Control Project has achieved major periodical
results, Chinese Premier Li Peng said here today.
</P>
<P>
In his speech delivered minutes after the successful daming
this morning, Li described the river damming as a gratifying
progress in taming the Yellow River, China's second longest.
</P>
<P>
Li, on behalf of the Central Committee of the Communist Party
of China (CPC), and the State Council, extended warm
congratulations and conveyed greetings to all Chinese and foreign
builders.
</P>
<P>
Vice Premier Jiang Chunyun declared the success of the river
damming at 10:28 am today. The damming process, started on Sunday,
lasted for more than 40 hours. 
</P>
</TEXT>
