presidential candidates.
</P>
<P>
Marchuk reiterated that he would remain faithful to social
democracy and that he would absorb experiences from social
democracies in Europe, and the Russian economic reforms, to align
Ukraine with European countries with advanced economies and
reliable social security.
</P>
<P>
Marchuk headed the Security Department, followed by one year's
service as the prime minister from June 1995 to May 1996.
</P>
<P>
