<HEADLINE> Kosovo Court Tries Ethnic Albanian Terrorists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, October 27 (Xinhua) -- A group of ethnic Albanians,
who have been allegedly engaged in terrorist acts, were brought on
trial today in the Kosovo autonomous province of Yugoslavia's
republic of Serbia.
</P>
<P>
A district court in Prishtina, capital of Kosovo, began the
trial today on 21 members of the "Liberation Force of Kosovo," an
illegal military organization which attempts to make Kosovo an
independent country.
</P>
<P>
They were charged with attacking policemen and civilians
repeatedly, killing three people and injuring many others,
reported Yugoslavia's Tanjug news agency.
</P>
<P>
This was the third group of members of outlawed terrorist
organizations being tried in a Prishtina court this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
