<HEADLINE> Museum Set up to Preserve Relics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, October 28 (Xinhua) -- A museum recently was completed
in the ancient city of Jiaohe, Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region,
to preserve hundreds of relics found there.
</P>
<P>
The 300 sq.m building was paid for with donations of 83,000 US
dollars from Japan, and nearly 50,000 US dollars from the local
government.
</P>
<P>
The design of the museum is Tang (618-907) style.
</P>
<P>
Jiaohe is located 10 km northwest of the city of Turpan in
Xinjiang. As one of the best-preserved ancient city ruins in the
world, with a history of more than 2,000 years, the place covers
an area of about 230,000 square meters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
