<DOCNO> XIE19971028.0294 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Panamanian Free Trade Zone's Re-Exports up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Panama's Free Zone of Colon
(FZC) registered a trade amount of 4.46 billion dollars on
re-exportation during the first three quarters of the year,
authorities reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Administration Office of the FZC said re-exports
increased by 12.3 percent from January to September 1997
compared with the same period 1996.
</P>
<P>
The commercial complex, considered the largest in Latin
America, registered 569,300 tons of goods traded.
</P>
<P>
The biggest share of re-exported merchandise through FZC came
from Asian markets.
</P>
<P>
The FZC dynamism is due to its location at the riverside of the
Canal of Panama, the channel for most of the world maritime
commerce from the Atlantic to the Pacific and vice versa.
</P>
<P>
The Panamanian government made recently a proposal to Latin
American countries that the FZC be the headquarters for the
upcoming World Free Trade Zone, as part of the Americas Free Trade
Agreement to be set up before 2005. 
</P>
</TEXT>
