<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tibet Keeps Clean Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The government of the Tibet
Autonomous Region has vowed to limit environmentally destructive
industries to maintain the region as one of the country's cleanest
places, said Xu Mingyang, vice-chairman of the regional government
in a recent interview.
</P>
<P>
Xu, in charge of environmental protection in Tibet, said
that the regional government has placed the promotion and
development of clean industries such as tourism and ethnic
handicrafts at the top of its list.
</P>
<P>
Economy at the cost of the environment will never happen
intentionally, today's China Daily quoted him as saying.
</P>
<P>
According to Xu, the regional government will take full account
of the needs of environmental protection when formulating
industry, energy, technology and economic policies.
</P>
<P>
He said the local government is working on a series of
regulations on pollution control in township enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The regional government has set environmental protection
requirements for existing large and medium-sized enterprises to
prevent them from discharging untreated wastes into the
surroundings.
</P>
<P>
An environmental protection committee has been set up to
coordinate and handle major environmental issues.
</P>
<P>
Environmental impact assessments have been done to all new,
large and medium-sized projects.
</P>
<P>
The regional government will also improve environment
monitoring and develop better environmental protection technology,
said Xu.
</P>
<P>
Tibet is currently one of the cleanest regions in China with
pure air, high transparency and a fairly good state of atmospheric
environmental quality. Acid rain has never occurred in the
region.
</P>
<P>
The water quality of the main rivers all over the region is
quite good and most of the lakes are in their primary state.
</P>
<P>
A latest survey on industrial pollution in the region has
revealed that most of the township enterprises pose no major
threat to the environment.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
