<HEADLINE> Unleaded Fuel Awareness Campaign Held in Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 27 (Xinhua) -- The use of unleaded fuel has
been in effect in Guangzhou, capital city of south China's
Guangdong province, since the beginning of this month.
</P>
<P>
In order to enhance public awareness of its importance, a
public outdoor campaign was co-sponsored by the Guangzhou
Environmental Protection Bureau and Opel, one of Europe's top car
manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
The Guangzhou City Government has issued several decrees,
including the Guangzhou Environmental Protection Regulations and
the Announcement on the Enhancement of the Administration of Motor
Vehicle Emissions, to increase awareness of pollution control
among its residents.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from Opel said they are working to design and
produce environmentally-friendly vehicles, and take the lead in
reducing noise pollution and the recycling of vehicles.  
</P>
