</P>
<P>
-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin said "Aloha!" to the American
people as he arrived at what he termed as the "major converging
point of cultures of the East and West" on Sunday to kick off his
state visit to the United States.
</P>
<P>
-- Russian President Boris Yeltsin will pay a state visit to
China next month to discuss with Chinese President Jiang Zemin the
progress of the development of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
-- The remains of Fang Yi, a former vice-premier of China's
State Council, were cremated in Beijing yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Fang died of illness on October 17 in Beijing at the age of
81. He was a battle-hardened Communist fighter, a proletarian
revolutionary, and an outstanding leader in the country's foreign
economic relations and in scientific and technological areas.
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- Only one-third of the damming remains to be done for the
Xiaolangdi Water Control Project, as the gap between the dam and
the north bank of Yellow River was narrowed from 106 to 39 meters
yesterday.
</P>
<P>
By 5 p.m., the earth and stone wall in the river stretched for
a length of 67.47 meters, narrowing the gap between it and the
north bank by two-thirds.
</P>
<P>
-- The 12th National Congress of the Chinese Peasants' and
Farmers' Democratic Party (CPFDP) opened yesterday in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The congress will study the report of the 15th National
Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC), review the CPFDP's
work in the past five years, amend the party constitution and
elect a new central committee of the party.
</P>
<P>
 "China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The Forbidden City in central Beijing, once the home of
emperors but now one of the world's most famous museums, is being
refurbished to restore it to its original look.
</P>
<P>
-- China's top legislators gathered in Beijing yesterday to
start a six-day session.
</P>
<P>
The agenda included the examination and approval of legislation
and the study of the speech deliveredly by Jiang Zemin at the 15th
National Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
-- Funding for the second phase of construction of the Three
Gorges Project has been guaranteed.  
</P>
