<HEADLINE> Fuzhou to Advance Cross-Straits Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The city of Fuzhou, capital of
Fujian Province in east China and the Chinese city nearest to
Taiwan, is ready for a new round of cross-straits cooperation,
according to Zhao Xuemin, a senior official from the provincial
government.
</P>
<P>
The city has made the most of the state's preferential policies
for conducting business with Taiwan. It has been authorized to
open direct flights to Taiwan and to set up experimental projects
with Taiwan investors.
</P>
<P>
Zhao said that in the coming days, the city will concentrate on
projects that will play an important role in promoting the
cross-straits cooperation.  
