<HEADLINE> '97 Fishing Zone Cultural Festival To Be Held in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, October 28 (Xinhua) -- '97 Fishing Zone Cultural
Festival will be held in Hui'an County, in east China's Fujian
Province, on Nov 17-18.
</P>
<P>
Fishing is one of the backbone industries in Hui'an, a coastal
county with a population of 900,000.
</P>
<P>
Last year, 200,000 tons of fish were caught.
</P>
<P>
Activities at the festival will include theatrical
performances, academic symposiums and exhibitions of books,
paintings and photos featuring the culture and customs in the
fishing zone.
</P>
<P>
Some commodities fairs selling mainly sea products, traditional
handicrafts and special local products will also be held. 
