<HEADLINE> 200 Shipments of Foreign Garbage Kept From Entering China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, October 28 (Xinhua) -- China stopped some 200 ships
carrying foreign garbage from entering the country last year,
according to a state environmental protection official.
</P>
<P>
Following the shocking exposure of imported chemical refuse in
1994, China has stepped up its checks and supervision on rubbish
imports and handled instances of illegal imports in Beijing,
Tianjin and Shanghai over the past years.
</P>
<P>
In January this year, the Shanghai judicial department handed
down a ten-year prison term to the man who organized the export of
garbage to China. The man, who was from the United States, was
expelled from China after paying a fine.  
</P>
</TEXT>
