PARIS, October 27 (Xinhua) -- The International Automobile
Fedreation (FIA) on Monday summoned former world champion Michael
Schumacher to appear before an extraordinary meeting of the World
Motor Sport Council, which will take place in Paris on November
11.
</P>
<P>
The Ferrari driver seemed to collided deliberately into
Canadian Jacques Villeneuve during the decisive last race of the
Formula One season in Jerez, Spain on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Schumacher could not continue after the accident while
Villeneuve finished the race and snatched the season's title.
</P>
<P>
Media in Schumacher's native Germany as well as Ferrari's home
Italy criticized Schumacher's "shameful driving". And Villeneuve
said in a TV interview that the German had "lost at his own game".
</P>
<P>
In 1994 at the Australian Grand Prix in Adelaide, Schumacher
collided with Damon Hill's Williams to defend his a one-point lead
in the championship. Schumacher finally won the championship.
</P>
</TEXT>
