<HEADLINE> Iran Earns 1.65 Billion Dollars in Non-oil Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Iran earned 1.65 billion
U.S. dollars from non-oil exports during the past six months, the
official news agency IRNA reported today.
</P>
<P>
This shows an increase of 18.1 percent compared with the same
period of last year, Ahmad Qassemi, director of the export
promotion department of the Industries Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The export of industrial products stood at 621 million
dollars, up by 21 percent, he said, adding that the exports
in this field is expected to earn for Iran some 1.79 billion
dollars by the end of the current Iranian fiscal year starting
from March 21.
</P>
<P>
He said that the export of metal and casting products brought
to the country 80.5 million dollars, and chemical and cellulosic
products 145 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
During the period, 187 million dollars of textiles were
exported, registering a growth of 21 percent compared with the
corresponding period of last year, Qassemi said.
</P>
<P>
Iran earned 132 million dollars from the export of foodstuffs,
pharmaceutical and sanitary products in the period, up by 27
percent, he added.
</P>
<P>
During the past years, the fall of oil price in world market
has added pressure to Iran's repayment of foreign debts. It has
made efforts to promote the export of non-oil products as
substitutes to oil. 
</P>
</TEXT>
